'''柑橘''' (pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'') is the Cantonese name for [[kumquat]].  In Mandarin Chinese it is pronounced ''gān jú'', literally "large tangerine orange."  The original name of this fruit in standard (Mandarin) Chinese, however, is [[金橘]] (''jīnjú'', literally "golden orange"), also pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'' in Cantonese.

